<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910723-0021</DOCNO><DOCID>910723-0021.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Homestake Mining Co.:   Company Expects to Report   Deficit for Second Quarter</HL><DATE>07/23/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   GLC HM T.GLC</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>PRECIOUS METALS, STONES, GOLD, SILVER (PCS)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Homestake Mining Co. said it expects to post a secondquarter net loss of about $69 million, or 69 cents a share,because of depressed gold prices and other problems.   In the year-earlier quarter, Homestake earned $37.3million, or 38 cents a share, including $45 million ofearnings from discontinued operations. Revenue in theyear-ago period was $127.8 million.</LP><TEXT>   Homestake, based in San Francisco, said it will havewrite-downs in the latest quarter totaling $62 million,including about $39 million related to mines in the U.S.,Chile and Western Australia. The company also said it willwrite off its entire remaining stake in certain Canadianmining companies, primarily Galactic Resources Ltd., totaling$12.5 million.   Analysts had been expecting write-downs in the quarter,but the amount of the charges was larger than some expected.Nonetheless, investors shrugged off the news. In trading onthe New York Stock Exchange yesterday, Homestake closed at$17.125, down 62.5 cents.</TEXT></DOC>